00:15:47,420 --> 00:15:49,290
I'm just going to make sure

264
00:15:49,290 --> 00:15:52,850
that you'll never be able
to open your mouth again.

265
00:15:52,850 --> 00:15:55,970
S-Stop!

266
00:16:00,430 --> 00:16:01,680
A shard of glass?

267
00:16:07,750 --> 00:16:09,710
J-Josuke Higashikata?!

268
00:16:10,100 --> 00:16:12,780
Why... And the shrimp, too?

269
00:16:13,310 --> 00:16:14,240
Hazamada!

270
00:16:14,240 --> 00:16:16,670
We finally caught up with you, asshole!

271
00:16:17,290 --> 00:16:19,420
But did you already forget?

272
00:16:19,420 --> 00:16:26,170
When you come face to face with
Show Off, you become a puppet, Josuke!

273
00:16:26,170 --> 00:16:28,130
Control him, Show Off!

274
00:16:28,130 --> 00:16:29,380
Don't be so sure about that.

275
00:16:33,640 --> 00:16:35,610
Wha... That shape...

276
00:16:36,260 --> 00:16:41,020
I didn't throw that shard to hit you.

277
00:16:41,430 --> 00:16:44,480
I threw it so I could put it
back in its original form!

278
00:16:44,500 --> 00:16:45,330
Swoosh

279
00:16:46,320 --> 00:16:47,940
M-My right hand!

280
00:16:48,250 --> 00:16:50,330
It turned back into wood!

281
00:16:50,330 --> 00:16:52,620
This isn't good, Hazamada!

282
00:16:52,620 --> 00:16:53,820
Calm down!

283
00:16:53,820 --> 00:16:56,030
Just pretend you have
your hand in your pocket!

284
00:16:56,030 --> 00:16:57,330
No one will notice!

285
00:16:57,990 --> 00:16:59,120
The real problem is

286
00:16:59,120 --> 00:17:03,410
that Jotaro should arrive at the station soon!

287
00:17:03,410 --> 00:17:05,750
I'm shocked that Josuke was safe,

288
00:17:05,750 --> 00:17:08,440
but let's give up on beating him right now!

289
00:17:08,440 --> 00:17:12,140
H-Hazamada! Wait for me!

290
00:17:13,050 --> 00:17:14,510
I see...

291
00:17:14,510 --> 00:17:16,890
So they're meeting him in front of the station.

292
00:17:16,890 --> 00:17:20,260
J-Josuke, we have no time to waste!

293
00:17:20,570 --> 00:17:24,390
The way they went is the fastest
way to get to the station!

294
00:17:25,130 --> 00:17:29,720
And that's why I've got you, Koichi.

295
00:17:36,640 --> 00:17:39,660
Looks like Josuke's not here yet.

296
00:17:40,800 --> 00:17:43,410
Can you see Josuke anywhere?

297
00:17:43,410 --> 00:17:44,960
Nope.

298
00:17:45,280 --> 00:17:49,640
If I see any sign of him,
I'll just take control of him.

299
00:17:49,640 --> 00:17:51,210
Don't worry!

300
00:17:51,320 --> 00:17:59,710
Ding Ding Ding Ding

301
00:17:53,380 --> 00:17:56,020
Hazamada! A train's coming through.

302
00:17:56,790 --> 00:17:58,450
The railroad crossing that
never lets you through!

303
00:17:58,450 --> 00:17:59,720
We'll have to wait a minute or two...

304
00:17:59,720 --> 00:18:02,050
All right. We'll go through the station building.

305
00:18:02,470 --> 00:18:04,980
No Crossing

306
00:18:02,470 --> 00:18:04,980
Emergency
Stop
Button

307
00:18:06,660 --> 00:18:10,510
Even if he catches up with us,
the train will stall Josuke!

308
00:18:10,510 --> 00:18:11,770
Just one more minute!

309
00:18:11,770 --> 00:18:14,850
I'll head over to the meeting spot first!

310
00:18:16,140 --> 00:18:17,670
I won!

311
00:18:19,070 --> 00:18:20,050
Huh?

312
00:18:23,490 --> 00:18:26,200
That's Josuke!

313
00:18:26,200 --> 00:18:28,320
Wh-What happened to the train?!

314
00:18:28,320 --> 00:18:30,420
Why's the crossing open?!

315
00:18:30,420 --> 00:18:32,000
Hazamada, look!

316
00:18:32,320 --> 00:18:36,220
Wh-What the hell is that Stand?!

317
00:18:37,110 --> 00:18:38,880
Ding Ding Ding Ding

318
00:18:39,430 --> 00:18:44,490
That was great! You see?
That's why I said I've got you.

319
00:18:47,290 --> 00:18:49,240
Ah! There he is!

320
00:18:50,180 --> 00:18:53,740
J-Jotaro! It's me, Josuke!

321
00:18:54,190 --> 00:18:55,140
Hey.

322
00:18:55,140 --> 00:18:56,530
We made it in time!

323
00:18:56,530 --> 00:18:59,770
We got Hazamada good, didn't we, Josuke?

324
00:19:00,490 --> 00:19:01,780
Did something happen?

325
00:19:09,330 --> 00:19:10,040
A copy?

326
00:19:10,800 --> 00:19:13,470
A Stand that copied you
down to your fingerprints?

327
00:19:13,470 --> 00:19:14,990
That's right!

328
00:19:14,990 --> 00:19:18,520
There would have been trouble
if he'd gotten here before me.

329
00:19:18,520 --> 00:19:20,990
But now we can relax.

330
00:19:20,990 --> 00:19:24,050
That copy bastard is missing
his right hand, so it'll be easy.

331
00:19:24,050 --> 00:19:26,930
I blew off his right hand.

332
00:19:26,930 --> 00:19:28,690
Use that to tell us apart.

333
00:19:28,690 --> 00:19:29,860
All right.

334
00:19:29,860 --> 00:19:32,350
They should get here at any moment.

335
00:19:34,860 --> 00:19:37,680
Huh? Why do I have this thing?

336
00:19:38,110 --> 00:19:42,170
Why did I get a pen out of Jotaro's pocket?

337
00:19:44,840 --> 00:19:46,780
I-I can't move!

338
00:19:46,780 --> 00:19:48,720
My arm just stopped moving on its own.

339
00:20:01,680 --> 00:20:04,200
O-On the other side of the glass...

340
00:20:04,660 --> 00:20:06,720
Th-That's...

341
00:20:11,350 --> 00:20:13,980
Josuke Higashikata...

342
00:20:13,980 --> 00:20:20,900
You're gonna stab Jotaro in the head
with that pen and kill him instantly.

343
00:20:20,900 --> 00:20:26,530
After all, if his death isn't instant,
your Shining Diamond will just fix him.

344
00:20:27,790 --> 00:20:31,590
Josuke! This is your fault
for getting outta line!

345
00:20:31,590 --> 00:20:37,380
I was just gonna halfway kill Jotaro
to chase him out of town.

346
00:20:37,380 --> 00:20:41,410
But now you're the one who'll kill Jotaro!

347
00:20:41,410 --> 00:20:44,240
It'll be all your fault!

348
00:20:50,930 --> 00:20:55,310
Now! Let him have it, Show Off!

349
00:20:56,310 --> 00:20:58,020
J-Jotaro...

350
00:20:58,380 --> 00:20:59,420
You bastard!

351
00:21:01,440 --> 00:21:03,400
Something wrong, Josuke?

352
00:21:03,400 --> 00:21:05,220
Huh? No...

353
00:21:06,060 --> 00:21:10,950
Looks like those guys finally found Hazamada.

354
00:21:13,040 --> 00:21:14,100
You little shit!

355
00:21:14,100 --> 00:21:18,780
You were just across the pedestrian bridge
at the station, just like that Josuke said.

356
00:21:18,780 --> 00:21:20,950
He's a great guy.

357
00:21:20,950 --> 00:21:25,330
He treated our wounds, and I'm not
even sure how, but they're all better!

358
00:21:26,390 --> 00:21:30,260
I'll make sure I pay you back in full for earlier.

359
00:21:30,260 --> 00:21:33,780
Let's take a little trip behind the restroom.

360
00:21:41,840 --> 00:21:45,250
That Stand is pretty
terrifying if it catches you.

361
00:21:45,630 --> 00:21:49,080
Well, I guess I'll break this doll now.

362
00:21:49,500 --> 00:21:51,680
It'll make me feel better.

363
00:22:01,140 --> 00:22:02,840
Meanwhile, unknown to anyone else,

364
00:22:02,840 --> 00:22:04,550
Tamami was admitted to the hospital.

365
00:22:16,630 --> 00:22:18,650
What a fool!

366
00:22:19,030 --> 00:22:21,600
Well, you have my condolences.

367
